136/*-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
137 FObjectDuplicationParameters.
138-----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
139
140/**
141 * This struct is used for passing parameter values to the StaticDuplicateObject() method. Only the constructor parameters are required to
142 * be valid - all other members are optional.
143 */
144struct FObjectDuplicationParameters
145{
146 /**
147 * The object to be duplicated
148 */
149 UObject* SourceObject;
150
151 /**
152 * The object to use as the Outer for the duplicate of SourceObject.
153 */
154 UObject* DestOuter;
155
156 /**
157 * The name to use for the duplicate of SourceObject
158 */
159 FName DestName;
160
161 /**
162 * A bitmask of EObjectFlags to propagate to the duplicate of SourceObject (and its subobjects).
163 */
164 EObjectFlags FlagMask;
165
166 /**
167 * A bitmask of EInternalObjectFlags to propagate to the duplicate of SourceObject (and its subobjects).
168 */
169 EInternalObjectFlags InternalFlagMask;
170
171 /**
172 * A bitmask of EObjectFlags to set on each duplicate object created. Different from FlagMask in that only the bits
173 * from FlagMask which are also set on the source object will be set on the duplicate, while the flags in this value
174 * will always be set.
175 */
176 EObjectFlags ApplyFlags;
177
178 /**
179 * A bitmask of EInternalObjectFlags to set on each duplicate object created. Different from FlagMask in that only the bits
180 * from FlagMask which are also set on the source object will be set on the duplicate, while the flags in this value
181 * will always be set.
182 */
183 EInternalObjectFlags ApplyInternalFlags;
184
185 /**
186 * Any PortFlags to be applied when serializing.
187 */
188 uint32 PortFlags;
189
190 EDuplicateMode::Type DuplicateMode;
191
192 /**
193 * if an object being duplicated as an assigned external package, the duplicated object will try to assign an associated package to itself.
194 * The associated package should come from the DuplicationSeed.
195 */
196 bool bAssignExternalPackages = true;
197
198 /**
199 * if this option is true, then PostLoad won't be called on the new duplicated objects.
200 * It will be the responsability of the caller in that case to eventually call post load on those objects. a `CreatedObjects` map should be provided.
201 */
202 bool bSkipPostLoad = false;
203
204 /**
205 * Optional class to specify for the destination object.
206 * @warning: MUST BE SERIALIZATION COMPATIBLE WITH SOURCE OBJECT, AND DOES NOT WORK WELL FOR OBJECT WHICH HAVE COMPLEX COMPONENT HIERARCHIES!!!
207 */
208 UClass* DestClass;
209
210 /**
211 * Objects to use for prefilling the dup-source => dup-target map used by StaticDuplicateObject. Can be used to allow individual duplication of several objects that share
212 * a common Outer in cases where you don't want to duplicate the shared Outer but need references between the objects to be replaced anyway.
213 *
214 * Objects in this map will NOT be duplicated
215 * Key should be the source object; value should be the object which will be used as its duplicate.
216 */
217 TMap<UObject*,UObject*> DuplicationSeed;
218
219 /**
220 * If non-null, this will be filled with the list of objects created during the call to StaticDuplicateObject.
221 *
222 * Key will be the source object; value will be the duplicated object
223 */
224 TMap<UObject*,UObject*>* CreatedObjects;
225
226 /**
227 * Constructor
228 */
229 COREUOBJECT_API FObjectDuplicationParameters( UObject* InSourceObject, UObject* InDestOuter );
230};

279 * Normally, you should call one of the FindObject or LoadObject functions instead.
280 *
281 * @param Outer The package to search within. If null, ObjectsReferenceString be a globally scoped path and this will be filled in with the actual package if found/created
282 * @param ObjectsReferenceString The object path string to resolve. If it is successfully resolved, this will be replaced with a path relative to Outer
283 * @param Create If true, it will try to load or create the required package if it is not in memory
284 * @param Throw If true, it will potentially raise an error if the object cannot be found
285 * @param LoadFlags Flags to use if Create is true and it needs to load a package, from the ELoadFlags enum
286 * @param InstancingContext The linker instancing context used to resolve package name during instacning (i.e. when a package file is loaded into a package with a different name)

504{

511/**
512 * Parse a reference to an object from a text representation
513 *
514 * @param Stream String containing text to parse
515 * @param Match Tag to search for object representation within string
516 * @param Class The class of the object to be found.
517 * @param DestRes Returned object pointer
518 * @param InParent Outer to search
519 * @oaran LoadingPolicy Controls whether the parse will attempt to load a fully qualified object reference, if needed.
520 * @param bInvalidObject [opt] Optional output. If true, Tag was matched but the specified object wasn't found.
521 *
522 * @return True if the object parsed successfully, even if object was not found
523 */
524COREUOBJECT_API bool ParseObject( const TCHAR* Stream, const TCHAR* Match, UClass* Class, UObject*& DestRes, UObject* InParent, EParseObjectLoadingPolicy LoadingPolicy, bool* bInvalidObject=nullptr );
525inline bool ParseObject( const TCHAR* Stream, const TCHAR* Match, UClass* Class, UObject*& DestRes, UObject* InParent, bool* bInvalidObject=nullptr )
526{

657/** Async package and object loading result */

659{
660 enum Type : uint8
661 {
662 /** Package or object failed to load */
663 Failed,
664 /** Package or object failed to load because it is missing */
665 FailedMissing,
666 /** Package or object failed to load due to a linker error */
667 FailedLinker,
668 /** Package or object failed to load because its data is not local */
669 FailedNotInstalled,
670 /** Package or object loaded successfully */
671 Succeeded,
672 /** Async loading was canceled */
673 Canceled
674 };
675}

677/** Async loading progress for a specific package */
678enum class EAsyncLoadingProgress : uint32
679{
680 /** Package failed to load */
681 Failed,
682 /** Package has started loading. */
683 Started,
684 /** Package I/O has been read. */
685 Read,
686 /** Package has finished its serialization phase. */
687 Serialized,
688 /** Package has finished all loading phase successfully */
689 FullyLoaded,
690 /** Async loading was canceled */
691 Canceled
692};

701 * @param Result Result of async loading.
702 */
703DECLARE_DELEGATE_ThreeParams(FLoadPackageAsyncDelegate, const FName& /*PackageName*/, UPackage* /*LoadedPackage*/, EAsyncLoadingResult::Type /*Result*/)
704
705/**
706 * Parameters passed to the FLoadPackageAsyncProgressDelegate callback.
707 */
708struct FLoadPackageAsyncProgressParams
709{
710 /* Name of the package. */
711 const FName PackageName { NAME_None };
712 /* Pointer to UPackage being loaded, can be nullptr depending on async loading progress. */
713 const UPackage* LoadedPackage { nullptr };
714 /* Progress of async loading. */
715 const EAsyncLoadingProgress ProgressType { EAsyncLoadingProgress::Failed };
716 /* Whether the current delegate should be released or destroyed when not required anymore. */
717 bool bReleaseDelegate { false };
718};
719
720/**
721 * Thread-safe delegate called on progress of async package loading.
722 */
723class FLoadPackageAsyncProgressDelegate
724{
725public:
726 using DelegateType = TTSDelegate<void(FLoadPackageAsyncProgressParams& Params)>;
727
728 FLoadPackageAsyncProgressDelegate(DelegateType&& InDelegate, uint32 InMask = MAX_uint32)
729 : Delegate(InDelegate)
730 , Mask(InMask)
731 {}
732
733 constexpr static inline uint32 BuildMask(EAsyncLoadingProgress Progress)
734 {
735 return 1 << (uint32)Progress;
736 }
737
738 constexpr static inline uint32 BuildMask(auto... Types)
739 {
740 return (0 | ... | BuildMask(Types));
741 }
742
743 void Invoke(FLoadPackageAsyncProgressParams& Params)
744 {
745 if (Mask & BuildMask(Params.ProgressType))
746 {
747 Delegate.ExecuteIfBound(Params);
748 }
749 }
750
751private:
752 TTSDelegate<void(FLoadPackageAsyncProgressParams& Params)> Delegate;
753 const uint32 Mask { MAX_uint32 };
754};

1588 /** Search for an override **/

1590 {
1591 for (int32 Index = 0 ; Index < Overrides.Num(); Index++)
1592 {

1596 }

1600 /** Element of the override array **/
1601 struct FOverride
1602 {
1603 FName ComponentName;
1604 const UClass* ComponentClass = nullptr;
1605 TUniquePtr<FOverrides> SubOverrides;
1606 bool bDoNotCreate = false;
1607 FOverride(FName InComponentName)
1608 : ComponentName(InComponentName)
1609 {
1610 }
1611
1612 FOverride& operator=(const FOverride& Other)
1613 {
1614 ComponentName = Other.ComponentName;
1615 ComponentClass = Other.ComponentClass;
1616 SubOverrides = (Other.SubOverrides ? MakeUnique<FOverrides>(*Other.SubOverrides) : nullptr);
1617 bDoNotCreate = Other.bDoNotCreate;
1618 return *this;
1619 }
1620
1621 FOverride(const FOverride& Other)
1622 {
1623 *this = Other;
1624 }
1625
1626 FOverride(FOverride&&) = default;
1627 FOverride& operator=(FOverride&&) = default;
1628 };

1639 {
1640 check(SubobjectInits[Index].Subobject != Subobject);

1653 }

2137/**
2138 * Determines whether the specified array contains objects of the specified class.
2139 *
2140 * @param ObjectArray the array to search - must be an array of pointers to instances of a UObject-derived class
2141 * @param ClassToCheck the object class to search for
2142 * @param bExactClass true to consider only those objects that have the class specified, or false to consider objects
2143 * of classes derived from the specified SearhClass as well
2144 * @param out_Objects if specified, any objects that match the SearchClass will be added to this array
2145 */
2146template <class T>
2147bool ContainsObjectOfClass( const TArray<T*>& ObjectArray, UClass* ClassToCheck, bool bExactClass=false, TArray<T*>* out_Objects=nullptr )
2148{
2149 bool bResult = false;
2150 for ( int32 ArrayIndex = 0; ArrayIndex < ObjectArray.Num(); ArrayIndex++ )
2151 {
2152 if ( ObjectArray[ArrayIndex] != nullptr )
2153 {
2154 bool bMatchesSearchCriteria = bExactClass
2155 ? ObjectArray[ArrayIndex]->GetClass() == ClassToCheck
2156 : ObjectArray[ArrayIndex]->IsA(ClassToCheck);
2157
2158 if ( bMatchesSearchCriteria )
2159 {
2160 bResult = true;
2161 if ( out_Objects != nullptr )
2162 {
2163 out_Objects->Add(ObjectArray[ArrayIndex]);
2164 }
2165 else
2166 {
2167 // if we don't need a list of objects that match the search criteria, we can stop as soon as we find at least one object of that class
2168 break;
2169 }
2170 }
2171 }
2172 }
2173
2174 return bResult;
2175}

2227/**
2228 * Iterator for arrays of UObject pointers
2229 * @param TObjectClass type of pointers contained in array
2230*/
2231template<class TObjectClass>
2232class TObjectArrayIterator
2233{
2234 /* sample code
2235 TArray<APawn *> TestPawns;
2236 ...
2237 // test iterator, all items
2238 for ( TObjectArrayIterator<APawn> It(TestPawns); It; ++It )
2239 {
2240 UE_LOG(LogUObjectGlobals, Log, TEXT("Item %s"),*It->GetFullName());
2241 }
2242 */
2243public:
2244 /**
2245 * Constructor, iterates all non-null, non pending kill objects, optionally of a particular class or base class
2246 * @param InArray the array to iterate on
2247 * @param InClass if non-null, will only iterate on items IsA this class
2248 * @param InbExactClass if true, will only iterate on exact matches
2249 */
2250 FORCEINLINE TObjectArrayIterator( TArray<TObjectClass*>& InArray, UClass* InClassToCheck = nullptr, bool InbExactClass = false) :
2251 Array(InArray),

2255 {
2256 Advance();
2257 }

2259 * Iterator advance
2260 */
2261 FORCEINLINE void operator++()
2262 {
2263 Advance();
2264 }

2266 FORCEINLINE explicit operator bool() const
2267 {
2268 return Index < Array.Num();

2295 /**
2296 * Removes the current element from the array, slower, but preserves the order.
2297 * Iterator is decremented for you so a loop will check all items.
2298 */
2299 FORCEINLINE void RemoveCurrent()
2300 {
2301 Array.RemoveAt(Index--);
2302 }

2304 * Removes the current element from the array, faster, but does not preserves the array order.
2305 * Iterator is decremented for you so a loop will check all items.
2306 */
2307 FORCEINLINE void RemoveCurrentSwap()
2308 {
2309 Array.RemoveSwap(Index--);
2310 }
2311
2312protected:
2313 /**
2314 * Dereferences the iterator with an ordinary name for clarity in derived classes
2315 * @return the UObject at the iterator
2316 */
2317 FORCEINLINE TObjectClass* GetObject() const
2318 {
2319 return Array(Index);
2320 }
2321 /**
2322 * Iterator advance with ordinary name for clarity in subclasses
2323 * @return true if the iterator points to a valid object, false if iteration is complete
2324 */
2325 FORCEINLINE bool Advance()
2326 {
2327 while(++Index < Array.Num())
2328 {
2329 TObjectClass* At = GetObject();
2330 if (
2331 IsValid(At) &&
2332 (!ClassToCheck ||
2333 (bExactClass
2334 ? At->GetClass() == ClassToCheck
2335 : At->IsA(ClassToCheck)))
2336 )
2337 {
2338 return true;
2339 }
2340 }
2341 return false;
2342 }
2343private:
2344 /** The array that we are iterating on */
2345 TArray<TObjectClass*>& Array;
2346 /** Index of the current element in the object array */
2347 int32 Index;
2348 /** Class using as a criteria */
2349 UClass* ClassToCheck;
2350 /** Flag to require exact class matches */
2351 bool bExactClass;
2352};

3470 * A macro that outputs a formatted message to log with a canonical reference to an asset if a given logging category is active at a given verbosity level
3471 * @param CategoryName name of the logging category

3480 CA_CONSTANT_IF((ELogVerbosity::Verbosity & ELogVerbosity::VerbosityMask) <= ELogVerbosity::COMPILED_IN_MINIMUM_VERBOSITY && (ELogVerbosity::Warning & ELogVerbosity::VerbosityMask) <= FLogCategory##CategoryName::CompileTimeVerbosity) \
3481 { \
3482 UE_LOG_EXPAND_IS_FATAL(Verbosity, PREPROCESSOR_NOTHING, if (!CategoryName.IsSuppressed(ELogVerbosity::Verbosity))) \
3483 { \
3484 ::UE::Core::Private::RecordAssetLog(CategoryName.GetCategoryName(), ELogVerbosity::Verbosity, ::UE::FAssetLog(Asset), FString::Printf(Format, ##__VA_ARGS__), __FILE__, __LINE__); \
3485 UE_LOG_EXPAND_IS_FATAL(Verbosity, \
3486 { \
3487 UE_DEBUG_BREAK_AND_PROMPT_FOR_REMOTE(); \
3488 FDebug::AssertFailed("", __FILE__, __LINE__, TEXT("%s: %s"), *FAssetMsg::FormatPathForAssetLog(Asset), *FString::Printf(Format, ##__VA_ARGS__)); \
3489 CA_ASSUME(false); \
3490 }, \
3491 PREPROCESSOR_NOTHING \
3492 ) \
